FT  08 APR 92 / UK Company News: Cadbury Schweppes buys Alma brands
Cadbury Schweppes has acquired the Hacks and Victory V brands from the
receivers of Alma Holdings for Pounds 3.08m cash.
The purchase price included the production equipment and the Angus
manufacturing facility in Dundee.
Hacks and Victory V are well-known brands in the UK medicated confectionery
market, estimated to be worth some Pounds 68m a year.
